============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Empiricism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   All knowledge comes from sensory experience; mind is blank slate
Philosopher:  Locke/Hume
Example:      We know fire burns because we felt it, not through pure reason

Concept:      Rationalism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Some knowledge is innate or derivable by reason alone
Philosopher:  Descartes/Spinoza
Example:      Math truths like 2+2=4 are known by reason, not experiment

Concept:      Plato's Theory of Forms
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Physical objects are imperfect copies of eternal abstract Forms
Philosopher:  Plato
Example:      The perfect circle exists only as a Form; drawn circles approximate it

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Elasticity
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Responsiveness of demand to price change
Formula:    PED = %dQd / %dP
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Gasoline demand inelastic; luxury goods elastic

Concept:    Supply and Demand
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Price determined where quantity supplied equals demanded
Formula:    P* where Qd=Qs
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Housing prices rise when population grows but supply stays fixed

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

